node.text:
Today we’re taking it to the field. You can also do this on a treadmill

1. 50 meter sprint 
-25 push ups
2. 50 meter sprint 
-8 cycle jumps each leg
3. 50 meter sprint 
-15 V ups
4. 50 meter sprint 
-7 broad jumps 
5. 50 meter sprint 
-30 shoulder taps.
6. 50 meter sprint 
-10 burpees jumps 

Rest 3 mins and repeat 2 more times.
@fitnessculturetraining @gymshark 
🎥 @alexluscombe_photography 
Song Astronaut in the Ocean by Masked Wolf #trackworkout #hiitworkout #fatlosscardio #circuittraining

Quick, easy, and can be done anywhere. 
100 air squats

It’s amazing how something so simple can leave you wiped out!

node.text:
You know this one was going to happen. Blonde bomber arm session after our back training! Over the years we had some legendary workouts and this one was up there! @shaunstafford 

Biceps 

1. DB curls in last pull down- 12,12,12. Use the pads from the lap pulldown machine as you would an arm blaster. Keep your elbows against the pad.

2. Hammer curls- 10,10,10

3. Spider curls, 5 half way up, 5 hallways down, 5 full reps. 3 sets
Superset 
4. Wide grip straight bar curls as many as possible 3 sets. Don’t let your partner beat you! 

Shorts -@gymshark 
Program- @fitnessculturetraining 
Fit band - @whoop

node.text:
Hi from Paradise! Little trip update, we are currently in Menorca Spain. We’ve been on the road for three months. Have visited five different countries now -Dubai-Maldives-Greece-England.
Currently waiting on Morgan’s K-1 fiancée visa so she can come into the US. No matter what we will be traveling back to our respective homes at the end of this month. I will be heading back to Utah and Morgan will be headed back to Australia until we get that visa. Once that happens Morgan will move over with her dog Loo Loo and we will look for a house. Can’t decide if we want to build or buy. Both options seem bad right now with the housing market LOL maybe will just rent an RV

node.text:
Shoulder day with a twist. Bodybuilding and a little Olympic lifting. 
Truth is I rather always have fun with my fitness. By that I mean I love crossing boundaries - Bodybuilding/aesthetics, strength/power and functional fitness all play a role in my training. I don’t want to be a one trick pony, and I like constantly trying new things. What is your favorite way to train? 

Start off each workout with 10 mins warm up. 

1. Hang Snatch -  4 @ 65%, 3 @ 75%, 2@78%, 2 @ 80%

2a. Arnold DB press- 8,8,8
Superset 
2b. Burpees over bar 12,12,12

3a. DB lateral raise - 10,10,10
3b. Bent over DB raise - 8,8,8
3c. KB upright row - 12,12,12
(Do each movement back to back before resting 90 sec between sets)

@fitnessculturetraining app with all our programs.
@gymshark 
@whoop

node.text:
Bring out the GUNS! Summer time got me adding in few extra sets of biceps!
These three are my go to for a compete and effective set.

For the long head
- single arm DB preacher curl.
8,8,8,8

For the Brachialis and forearms 
-neutral grip plate curls (keep wrist straight) 
12,10,8,

For the short head 
-Super man cable curl
15,15,15

Shirt and shorts - @gymshark 
Training program - @fitnessculturetraining 
Recovery and workout - @whoop
